blocks.name: dfon2lem4
blocks.content: Lemma for ~ dfon2 . If two sets satisfy the new definition, then one is a subset of the other. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 25-Feb-2011.)
blocks.origin:
thm dfon2lem4(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wa(wal(s0, wi(wa(wpss(cv(s0), c0), wtr(cv(s0))), wcel(cv(s0), c0))), wal(s1, wi(wa(wpss(cv(s1), c1), wtr(cv(s1))), wcel(cv(s1), c1)))), wo(wss(c0, c1), wss(c1, c0)))
  -| wcel(c0, universe)
  -| wcel(c1, universe)
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
} = {
  a1ii(wi(wa(wal(s0, wi(wa(wpss(cv(s0), c0), wtr(cv(s0))), wcel(cv(s0), c0))), wal(s1, wi(wa(wpss(cv(s1), c1), wtr(cv(s1))), wcel(cv(s1), c1)))), wo(wss(c0, c1), wss(c1, c0))), diffss(s0, s1))
  sylibr(wa(wal(s0, wi(wa(wpss(cv(s0), c0), wtr(cv(s0))), wcel(cv(s0), c0))), wal(s1, wi(wa(wpss(cv(s1), c1), wtr(cv(s1))), wcel(cv(s1), c1)))), wo(wss(c0, c1), wss(c1, c0)), wo(wceq(cin(c0, c1), c0), wceq(cin(c0, c1), c1)))

blocks.name: dfon2lem7
blocks.content: Lemma for ~ dfon2 . All elements of a new ordinal are new ordinals. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 25-Feb-2011.)
blocks.origin:
thm dfon2lem7(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wal(s0, wi(wa(wpss(cv(s0), c0), wtr(cv(s0))), wcel(cv(s0), c0))), wi(wcel(c1, c0), wal(s1, wi(wa(wpss(cv(s1), c1), wtr(cv(s1))), wcel(cv(s1), c1)))))

blocks.content: Lemma for ~ dfon2 . The intersection of a nonempty class ` A ` of new ordinals is itself a new ordinal and is contained within ` A ` (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 26-Feb-2011.)

blocks.content: ` On ` consists of all sets that contain all its transitive proper subsets. This definition comes from J. R. Isbell, "A Definition of Ordinal Numbers", American Mathematical Monthly, vol 67 (1960), pp. 51-52. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 20-Feb-2011.)
